The metrics determines the number of possible branches in the method's execution path. An empty method has a cyclomatic complexity of 1. Each occurrence of one of the following elements increases the cyclomatic complexity by 1:\
- while\
- do-while\
- for\
- if\
- one case of a switch statement\
- catch clause\
- conditional operator (aka. ? : operator)\
- conditional boolean operators (&& and ||)\
\
The statistic limits the allowed cyclomatic complexity to 5. \
